freedesktop-sdk-23.08beta.1:
  * freedesktop-sdk is now "bootstrappable"
    This means freedesktop-sdk doesnt depend on previous freedesktop-sdk versions
    to build, but it uses instead freedesktop-sdk-binary-seed for its bootstrap
    to depend on the minimal binary seed possible.
    See https://bootstrappable.org/ for more info
  * ppc64le is again a supported architecture
  * Update all the components to the latest version available, check specific
    versions at https://gitlab.com/freedesktop-sdk/freedesktop-sdk/-/wikis/Release-Contents#contents
  * freedesktop-sdk project has been ported to buildstream 2
  * A lot of other small fixes and improvements

